Not as far as I know. You can get KSPRC and Astronomer's packs working, with a bit of fiddling - although Astronomer's pack seems to be more difficult from a quick glance through the thread. I use KSPRC myself. You can almost all of it working nicely if you dig around in the thread for the instructions.

If all you're after is the clouds, atmospheres and city lights, then I think all you need to do is install the "BoulderCo" folder from KSPRC and leave everything else out. (IIRC, there's an unnecessary ATM configs folder in the BoulderCo folder as well, which can be deleted.)
